:::.col-12 .col-md-6
### The Sun: 

* **Type &amp; Appearance:** The Sun is a `middle`-sized, `yellow`-coloured star.
* **Energy Source:** It acts as the `original source of heat and light` for the Earth, all other planets, and their respective satellites.
* **Dimensions &amp; Mass:**
* **Diameter:** Approximately `13 lakh and 84 thousand` kilometers ($1,384,000\text{ km}$).
* **Mass:** $1.99 \times 10^{33}\text{ Kilograms}$.
:::
:::
</md></sn><sn><md>### Profile of the Eight Planets

`Eight planets` move around the Sun, ordered here from nearest to furthest. The ++first four++ (Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, Jupiter, and Saturn) are `quite bright` and can be observed without instruments, while ++the final two++ `require a telescope`.

+++ view

![img](https://i.pinimg.com/736x/38/59/68/385968d53de96c17aaced39c74e6c401.jpg)

+++
</md></sn><sn><md>:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-8
### Mercury

* **Position &amp; Size:** The `smallest and nearest` planet to the Sun.
* **Distance &amp; Diameter:** Average distance from the sun is `5.8` crore kilometers ($58,000,000\text{ km}$); its diameter measures `4,850` kilometers.
* **Orbit:** Takes `88 days` to complete one trip around the Sun, meaning one year on Mercury equals 88 Earth days.
* **Surface &amp; Environment:** Because it is so `close to the Sun`, intense light occasionally renders it invisible. Its `gravity is too weak` to retain an atmosphere, meaning there is `no air, water, rain, or clouds—making life` impossible. Photos captured by the American *Mariner-10* spacecraft in 1974 revealed a `cratered surface looking very much like Earth's moon`.
* **Satellites:** Mercury has `no satellites`.
