:::.col-12 .col-md-6
#### Mars

* **Position:** The nearest planetary `neighbour to Earth`.
* **Distance &amp; Diameter:** Lies at an average distance of `22.8` crore kilometers ($228,000,000\text{ km}$) from the Sun, with a diameter of `6,787` kilometers.
* **Orbit &amp; Day:** Takes `687 days` to orbit the Sun, though its `length of day and night is nearly equal to Earth's`.
* **Environment:** ++Life cannot survive++ here due to a severe `scarcity of water` and a very `high level of carbon dioxide` in the air.
* **Satellites:** Has two satellites: `Phobos and Deimos`.
:::
:::
</md></sn><sn><md>:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
#### Jupiter

* **Size:** The `largest planet` in the solar system—so massive that it is `1,300 times larger than Earth`.
* **Distance &amp; Diameter:** Located `77.8` crore kilometers ($778,000,000\text{ km}$) away from the Sun, boasting a massive diameter of `1,42,984` kilometers.
* **Orbit:** Takes `4,331` Earth days to complete one single orbit around the Sun.
* **Atmosphere:** Composed primarily of gases like `hydrogen and helium`.
* **Satellites:** Jupiter has `97 satellites`.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://news.ucr.edu/sites/default/files/2022-07/jupiter_rings_bright.jpg)
:::
:::

