:::.col-12 .col-md-6
#### Neptune

* **Distance &amp; Diameter:** The `most distant planet`, sitting roughly `450 crore kilometers` ($4,500,000,000\text{ km}$) away from the Sun. Its diameter measures `48,400` kilometers.
* **Orbit &amp; Environment:** Because it is so far away, light and heat from the sun are minimal. Its ++total surface area++ is as large as `72 Earths combined`, and its ++atmosphere++ is composed of `methane and ammonia`. It takes `165 Earth years` to circumnavigate the sun once.
* **Satellites:** Neptune has `14 satellites`.
:::
:::
