| **Neptune** | Most distant planet; total area is as large as 72 Earths; receives minimal heat and light. | About 450 crore | 48,400 | 165 years | Methane and Ammonia | 14 |</md></sn><sn><md>### Size and Shape of the Earth

The exact true shape and physical dimensions of the Earth were heavily debated throughout history. Absolute visual proof arrived on `April 12, 1961`, when `Russian astronaut Yuri Gagarin` orbited the planet. His observations and photographs confirmed the real shape of the Earth.

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-8
* **True Shape:** The Earth is an `oblate spheroid` —meaning it is `fundamentally round`, but ++slightly flattened++ at the `North and South` poles, with a slight ++bulge++ along the `East-West equator`.
* **Dimensional Discrepancy:** Because it is not a perfect sphere, its `dimensions differ by region`:
* **Actual Equatorial (East-West) Diameter:** 12,714 km *(Note: Text states 12,714 km for equatorial and 12,751 km for polar)*.
* **Actual Polar (North-South) Diameter:** 12,751 km.
:::

